HEADWORD: May laws
<hw>May laws</hw>. <sn>1.</sn> <def>See <er>Kulturkampf</er>,
above.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In Russia, severe oppressive laws against Jews,
which have given occasion for great persecution; -- so called because
they received the assent of the czar in May, 1882, and because likened
to the Prussian May laws (see <er>Kulturkampf</er>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mayonnaise</ent>⟦br⟧
